He believed in his motto that many of the world's problems can be solved easily if people want to think.
His slogan, "Think!", thus became the image around which the life of the future giant was unfolding (as well as the name of his internal magazine, which IMB began to publish in 1935).
Moreover, it was the basis of a corporate culture that Watson carefully built.
"For us in IBM, long-term thinking means constant movement to the future.
IBM survived and flourished for a hundred years because it remained faithful to its original values, although it was not afraid to change everything around it.
In our first 100 years, this has enabled us to transform technology, business, and company.
In the second hundred years, we hope to achieve even more,” says Samuel J. Palmizano, the current head of the company, on the occasion of the Jubilee.
Complex system
