Almost no one understands what's going on or why we have to fight in this war.
“The lack of facts,” observes Mr. Englund, “is filled with guesses, assumptions, hopes, fears, obsessive ideas, conspiracy theories, dreams, nightmares, and rumors.”
Beauty and Pilgrimage traces the fate of people like Florence Pharmborough, an English nurse in the Russian army, and Richard Stumpf, a young mariner of the German High Seas Navy.
Their stories are drawn mainly from memoirs, letters and other material already published.
