On innovation as a form of art:
"The great idea from the great product separates a huge number of skillful work ... when you twist the great idea, it changes and grows."
You'll learn a lot about her finesse.
There are compromises that you need to make -- some of the things you can't make electrons, glass, robots, or factories.
