In the end, it's all about taste - it's all about trying to express yourself to the best that humans have ever made, and later to try to bring it into what you do.
Picasso said good artists copy, great artists steal.
We've always been ashamed to steal great ideas.
Part of what made MacIntosh famous was that the people who worked on it were musicians, poets, artists, zoologists, historians who had become the best information technology experts in the world.
